    "faq": {
      "type": "lsc-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What are exosomes",
            "answer": "<p>Exosomes are microscopic extracellular vesicles that act as cellular messengers. They help regulate communication between cells, supporting repair processes, collagen production, and overall skin regeneration.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is EXO|E?",
            "answer": "<p>EXO|E is a clinically developed exosome-based regenerative complex designed for professional aesthetic use. It is applied using advanced delivery techniques such as microneedling to enhance skin renewal and improve overall skin quality.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "is Exosome therapy injectable?",
            "answer": "<p>No. In our clinic, EXO|E is applied topically and delivered into the skin using precision microneedling. It is not used as a traditional injectable filler or volumising treatment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How is exosome therapy different from dermal fillers?",
            "answer": "<p>Dermal fillers add volume and structure to specific areas of the face.</p><p>Exosome therapy focuses on improving skin quality by supporting collagen production, texture refinement, and overall skin health.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How is it different from polynucleotides?",
            "answer": "<p>Polynucleotides primarily stimulate tissue repair and hydration through DNA-based regeneration.</p><p>Exosomes act as signalling messengers that support broader cellular communication, collagen renewal, and skin recovery.</p><p>They can sometimes complement each other depending on treatment goals.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What concerns do exosome therapy treat?",
            "answer": "<p>Exosome therapy may help improve:</p><p>• Dull or tired-looking skin</p><p>• Uneven texture</p><p>• Fine lines</p><p>• Enlarged pores</p><p>• Loss of firmness</p><p>• Skin recovery following laser or microneedling</p><p>It is focused on overall skin rejuvenation rather than structural lifting or volume.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_7": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many sessions will I need?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients benefit from a course of 3–4 treatments spaced 3–4 weeks apart.</p><p>Your practitioner will tailor the plan to your skin condition and goals.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_8": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "When will I see results?",
            "answer": "<p>Some clients notice improved hydration and glow within the first week.</p><p>More significant improvements in firmness and texture develop gradually over 4–12 weeks as collagen renewal continues.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_9": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is the treatment painful?",
            "answer": "<p>A topical numbing cream is applied prior to microneedling to ensure comfort. Most clients describe the sensation as mild and tolerable.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_10": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will it make me look different?",
            "answer": "<p>Exosome therapy improves skin quality rather than facial structure. The goal is healthier, smoother, more radiant skin not a “done” or overtreated appearance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_11": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do results last?",
            "answer": "<p>Results vary by individual. After completing a course, many clients choose maintenance treatments every 4–6 months to support ongoing collagen production and skin health.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_12": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What payment options do you offer?",
            "answer": "<p>We offer flexible payment options to make your treatment as convenient as possible. You can choose to pay per single session or pay in full for a course of treatments for better overall value. We accept card, cash, and bank transfer in clinic.</p><p>For added flexibility, we also offer 0% finance through Klarna, allowing you to spread the cost into manageable instalments with a range of payment options available, subject to eligibility.</p><p>If you’re unsure which option is best for you, our team will be happy to guide you.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_13": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who is NCFT suitable for?",
            "answer": "<p>NCTF is suitable for anyone experiencing dullness, dehydration, fine lines, or a loss of skin radiance.<br/><br/>It’s ideal for people who want fresher, healthier-looking skin without fillers or surgery, and can be used on the face, neck, hands, or décolletage.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_14": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is your cancellation policy?",
            "answer": "<p>Cancellations up to 24 hours before your appointment will receive a full refund or can be rescheduled.<br/><br/>Any cancellations on the day can be rescheduled but will not be refunded.<br/><br/>If you do not show to your appointment you will not receive a refund or a reschedule. Please note that we offer email and text appointment reminders right up until 24 hours before your appointment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_15": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "I would like to speak to someone before I book my treatment, how is best to do this?",
            "answer": "<p>If you would like to speak to someone please do one of the below.<br/><br/>- Use the enquiry button.<br/><br/>- Contact us via email at info@laserskinclinics.co.uk<br/><br/>- Call us during opening hours on 01902 256667<br/><br/>- Send us a WhatsApp by clicking the WhatsApp button on the website.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_16": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do I need to book a consultation before my first session?",
            "answer": "<p>No you don't your consultation is done on the day of your treatment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_17": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does it hurt?",
            "answer": "<p>The procedure is quick and well-tolerated.</p><p>You may feel a slight prickling sensation during the injections, but a topical numbing cream can be applied beforehand to ensure comfort throughout the session.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_18": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "When will I see results?",
            "answer": "<p>You’ll see increased hydration and glow within days, with progressive improvements in firmness and texture over the following weeks as collagen production increases.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_19": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there any downtime?",
            "answer": "<p>Downtime is minimal.<br/><br/>You may notice slight redness or tiny marks at the injection points, which usually settle within a few hours.<br/><br/>Most clients return to normal activities the same day.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_20": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do results last?",
            "answer": "<p>Results can last up to 6 months, depending on your skin type, age, and lifestyle.</p><p>Many clients choose to maintain their results with regular top-up sessions throughout the year.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_21": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many sessions will I need?",
            "answer": "<p>We usually recommend a course of 3 sessions spaced 2 to 4 weeks apart for optimal results.<br/><br/>After your initial course, maintenance treatments every 3 to 6 months help to keep the skin hydrated and radiant.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
